You can help by adding missing items with reliable sources.)

You can help by adding missing items with reliable sources.)

http://dbpedia.org/property/desc.value: The product tanker collided with a breakwater at the Kaohsiung port, and started taking on water, causing a heavy list.

The lightering cargo ship sank in the estuary of the Meghna River in Lakshmipur, Bangladesh, after hitting an underwater object. The ship rested on bottom of the sea canal with superstructure remaining above waterline. All 12 crew rescued.

The sand barge capsized and sank after colliding with passenger launch  on the Meghna River at 11 PM. One crew member, who, according to survivor testimony, was trapped in the vessel as it sank, was missing, and local emergency services conducted a search for him.
The ro-ro ferry rolled onto her port side and sank partially above water at dock at Kumai port, South Kalimantan, Borneo, Indonesia.

The decommissioned  guided missile frigate was sunk during a sinking exercise , as part of a multinational exercise Rim of the Pacific  2022, approximately  northwest of Kauai, Hawaii. She was hit by Paveway laser-guided bombs dropped by U.S. Navy F/A-18E/F Super Hornets and United States Marine Corps F-35C Lightning II aircraft from Carrier Air Wing 9 operating from the aircraft carrier . U.S., Canadian, Australian, and Malaysian aircraft all attacked the target, sinking her in  of water in the Pacific Ocean.

The fishing trawler capsized  off the coast of Mahaicony, Guyana. One of the four crew was able to enter a lifeboat and was rescued by nearby fishermen, while the other three were still missing. The country's government was investigating the incident, and the coast guard continued searching for the three missing men, who were thought to be trapped underneath the vessel.
The tourism catamaran caught fire, burned out and sank in the Galápagos Islands. All 25 on board were rescued.
The urchin fishing boat capsized during rough weather in the Santa Barbara Channel. The one crewman swam for five hours before eventually making it to an oil rig, after which he was rescued.
The cargo ship suffered cargo shift at anchor in heavy swells causing her to capsize and sink off Hải Phòng, Vietnam. Her 8 crew and 2 passengers were rescued.

The product tanker grounded near Praia Islet shortly after departing the port of Praia da Graciosa. Its crew of 12 were safe, and the ship was stabilized. Its owners are looking to have the ship refloated and towed away for repairs.
The cargo ship sank in shallow water with upper deck above water off Hải Phòng, Vietnam possibly due to a typhoon. Crew safe.
The trawler sank at its mooring in the Keelbeg Pier, Union Hall, Ireland, causing a spill of hydraulic fluid and diesel fuel.
A  fishing vessel was sunk in a collision with the bulk carrier    east of the Yangtze River estuary. Three crew were rescued, 11 crewmembers remain missing.
The general cargo ship sank after colliding with the oil tanker    southeast of Taitung, Taiwan off the southeast Taiwan coast. Her crew were all rescued by the Taiwan Coast Guard.
The product tanker sank in the Gulf of Siam  north of Koh Samui Island, Thailand. Her six crew were rescued.
The passenger ro-ro ship reported sinking in stormy weather in the Arabian Sea off the coast of Oman.
A boat capsized on a voyage from Nirsa to Jamtara at about 7:00 PM on the Damodar River. 17 were aboard; five were rescued, and 12 were missing.

A migrant boat sank  off of Key Largo, United States. All 10 on board were rescued. Six of the migrants were repatriated to Cuba, while the other four were brought to hospital for injuries. The incident is suspected to be related to human smuggling operations.
The cargo ship capsized and sank in the Taiwan Strait some  west north west of Taichung, Taiwan after being caught in rough weather. 7 rescued, 1 missing.
The sailing yacht sank at a pier when rammed by the tug    at Tarragona, Spain. The tug suffered a control problem while backing resulting in the high speed ramming, crushing the yacht's side.
A migrant boat sank off the coast of Zarzis, Tunisia after departing from Libya on a voyage to Italy. Of the estimated 70 people aboard, six died, 34 were rescued, and another 30 were missing.
The cargo ship sank in rough weather in Fujian Province waters in the Taiwan Strait. All 13 crew were rescued.
Several houseboats and shikaras either sank or were destroyed by snowfall on the Jhelum River near Srinagar, India, and in its Dal Lake.
The tugboat sank in the Adriatic Sea  off Bari, Italy. The captain was rescued, 3 dead, the other 2 crew missing. A float she was towing with 11 on board was later towed into port.

The  mussel-farming barge sank while moored during a storm. It currently lies  below the waterline. A salvage attempt had to be cancelled due to poor weather conditions, but new salvage operations are currently being planned, and the vessel is scheduled to return to service by June.
The barge while under tow was sunk in a collision with the container ship   in poor visibility in the Bangkok approach channel near red buoy No. 23, Samut Prakan waters. Crew safe.
The cargo ship reported sinking in the Ionian Sea. The crew abandoned ship.
The cargo ship capsized and sank at Alexandria, Egypt in rough weather.
A barge, that had been deck cargo aboard the cargo ship  , sank after being lost overboard in rough seas between Juan Fernandez Islands, Chile and Puerto Montt, Chile.
A  yacht went aground on rocks and sank in bad weather at Lammermoor Beach, Queensland, Australia.

Tropical Storm Megi: The ro-ro ferry submerged while it was docked at the Consuelo Port in Camotes Islands, Cebu. There were no passengers on board the vessel when the incident happened. All 14 crew members managed to abandon the ship before it went down.
The cargo ship was sunk in a collision with   in the South China Sea off Tam Quan, Vietnam. Nine crew rescued by Vinafco 28, one missing.
The fishing boat sank  south of Kê Gà Cape, Bình Thuận. 2 of her crew were rescued, 3 were killed.
Typhoon Nalgae: The cement carrier lost power and sank in rough seas on the east side of the Changhua wind farm channel south west of Taiwan. Five crew were rescued, 12 crewmembers remain missing.
Tropical Storm Megi: The coaster capsized and sank in Ormoc Bay, Leyte, Philippine Islands. Crew fate unknown.
The product tanker ran aground at the Port at Kavaratti on its maiden voyage.
The  was noticed to be on fire at around 4 PM. The Keelung City Fire Department and military personnel extinguished the fire soon after.
A motorboat, carrying 85 people fleeing floods in Anambra State, sank in the Niger River when it struck a submerged bridge. There were 76 deaths.
The decommissioned tugboat was scuttled as an artificial reef in the Gulf of Mexico  off East Pass, Destin, Florida.
The yacht caught fire, burned out and sank after a possible explosion at Princess Pier in Torquay, Devon, UK.
The patrol boat operated by the Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency sank in the harbour of Lagos, Nigeria.
The coaster developed a list and sank in a storm in  of water off Saumlaki Harbour, in the Tanimbar Islands, in the Timor Sea. Her crew of 15 swam to shore and were safe.

A motorized panga ran aground near the Ocean Beach Pier in San Diego, United States. No people were found onboard, but about six life vests and some other items were recovered from the boat. U.S. Customs and Border Protection investigated the scene, believing the vessel to have possibly been used in smuggling drugs or people into the country.

A trawler, with 14 aboard, developed a hole in its hull and capsized on the Meghna River. Four people, a grandmother and three of her grandchildren drowned, while the other 10 were injured, and taken to a local hospital for treatment.

thumb|Baragoola The then 99-year-old ferry quickly sank at her moorings after a decade of being poorly maintained. Two people were aboard, and left the vessel soon after it started taking on water. The vessel is slated to be disassembled and scrapped, as refloating is considered impossible.

The fish carrier ran aground and partially sank in southern Chile, some  west of Punta Arenas. The ship is resting on the bottom, capsized on starboard side and partially submerged. 13 crew went into life rafts and were rescued.
A fishing vessel was sunk in a collision with    and sank in the East China Sea  south of Jeju Island, South Korea. Her eight crew were rescued.
The cargo ship ran aground on the northwest Crete coast in Kissamos Bay in a storm, reportedly broke in half. Her 10 crew were rescued.
The vehicle carrier was sunk in a collision with   in the Bangka Strait, Bangka Belitung Islands. All 17 crew rescued.
The ship sank at dock in shallow water at Papeete due to a valve being left open.
The ro-ro ship capsized and sank in the Persian Gulf  from Asaluyeh, Iran in rough weather. 29 of 30 crew were rescued.
The inter-island ferry caught fire while approaching Batangas City, Philippines. All 85 people on board, including 47 passengers and 38 crew, were safely rescued.

The  fishing vessel was sunk in a collision with the container ship    off the coast of Virginia,  north east of Norfolk, Virginia, in the Atlantic Ocean. 12 on board went into a life raft and were picked up by  , her captain was taken off by a United States Coast Guard helicopter.
The fishing vessel was sunk in a collision with the container ship    east of Vũng Tàu, Vietnam. Her 4 crew were rescued by Morning Vinafco.
A catamaran capsized during a race off of Key West, United States. Two people were rescued.

The cargo ship was struck, broke in two, and sunk by an unknown ship west of Penghu, Taiwan, in the Taiwan Strait. Nine crew were rescued, two were killed, her captain and one crewmember remain missing.
A fishing vessel was sunk in a collision with the cargo ship    off Ravenna, Italy. Mika rescued her five-man crew.
The laid up specialized fishing vessel was beached, laying on her port side, by heavy swells on Oquendo Beach, Callao, Peru.
A  fishing boat burned to the waterline  west of Manzanita, Oregon. The sole crewman aboard was rescued from the water.
The push tug sank between the Penghu islands and the western Taiwan coast in the Taiwan Strait. All six crew missing.
A migrant vessel carrying mainly Haitian migrants sank around  north of Desecheo Island, Puerto Rico. 38 people were saved by the United States Coast Guard.
The fishing boat sank  south of Cồn Cỏ, Quảng Trị. Her 11 crew were rescued.
The  sailboat, that burned out in December 2021, was sunk as an artificial reef  south-south-west of East Pass, Destin, Florida in  of water in the Gulf of Mexico.
The  cabin cruiser burned in the Piscataqua River near New Castle, New Hampshire.
Two migrant boats capsized off the coast of Almeria, Spain, at night. 16 people were rescued, three bodies were recovered, and 10 remain missing.

The cargo ship became flooded in her engine room in the Kertch Strait. She was on a voyage from Istanbul, Turkey to Rostov-on-Don. Unclear if she was hit by a rogue wave, or a casualty of the 2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine.
The car carrier developed a list and was run aground to prevent capsizing off Tuapse, Russia, in the Black Sea.
The cargo ship sank in shallow water, mostly above water, in Linjiang River when she collided with the Linjiang Bridge.
The tuna fishing vessel went ashore at Pointe aux Sables, Mauritius, some  west of Port Louis. The crew made it to shore.
The fishing vessel was driven ashore at the Nuku’alofa wharf after multiple tsunamis barreled into Tongatapu, Tonga coastline within minutes of the Hunga Tonga–Hunga Ha'apai volcano's explosion.

A day after a close call running aground, the purse seiner sank in the Haro Strait off San Juan Island. All five crew members were rescued by two nearby purse seiners. The resulting diesel spill became an environmental disaster threatening the southern resident orcas living in nearby waters, leading to a weeks-long cleanup effort by the Coast Guard, the Washington State Department of Ecology, San Juan Office of Emergency Management, and the Swinomish Tribe.
A finished, but not yet delivered to owner, luxury  yacht burned out, or was heavily damaged, at Ferretti shipyard, Cattolica, Italy.
Typhoon Chaba: The cargo ship was beached in Yangjiang City, Yangxi County, Guangdong Province, China in the South China Sea.

The cargo ship was damaged in a collision with chemical tanker    off Kushimoto, Wakayama Prefecture, southeastern Honshu, Japan. She sailed or was towed into a bay off Shionomisaki and run aground to prevent sinking.

The  yacht caught fire while cruising the marine reserve of Es Freus, situated between Ibiza and Formentera, Spain. The yacht was towed to port, and the fire was extinguished, but the vessel capsized.
A migrant boat collided with a trawler on a voyage from Libya. Five passengers fell out of the boat in the collision, but only two were able to re-embark.
The coastal container ship listed, then capsized and sank  off Sai Ri Sawi Beach, Chumphon Province, Thailand, in the Gulf of Thailand. All ten crew were rescued by fishing vessels.
A boat ran aground and capsized off the Florida Keys, United States. Of the estimated 300 migrants aboard, 163 swam to shore.
Seven cargo dhows burned out at Nakhl Taghi port, Bushehr Province, Iran.
The decommissioned cargo ship was bombed and sunk as a target by a US Air Force F-15E Strike Eagle in the Gulf of Mexico in the Eglin Gulf Test and Training Range.

The tanker capsized and sank  north of Aruba in the Caribbean Sea in bad weather. 9 survivors rescued by cargo ship Melba , and 5 by UBC Stavanger , the ship's dog was also rescued. Her captain died after being rescued and 2 others remained missing.
The motor yacht sank at Unije, Croatia. All four people on board survived.
The container ship capsized and sank on her port side partially above water at berth at Shunan's Port, Honshu, Japan in Tokuyama Bay. The three crew aboard at the time are safe.

The decommissioned  Tariq-class frigate, believed to be Khaibar or Tariq, was sunk as a target in the northern Arabian Sea by a missile from an aircraft and a missile or torpedo from a submarine in a live-fire exercise.
The  ran aground in the Archipelago Sea, off Turku, Finland. Her hull was holed.
Capsizing of the Villa de Pitanxo: The  fishing vessel iced up, capsized and was lost off of Newfoundland, Canada. Of her crew of 24, three were rescued, 10 died, and another 11 were missing.
The derelict cargo ship sank in the Gulf of Siam  off Nakhon Si Thammarat Province south of Koh Samui, Thailand in  of water whilst under tow of a Royal Thai Navy vessel.
A migrant boat capsized in the Atlantic Ocean on a voyage from North Africa to an unknown destination. 32 people were rescued, one body was recovered, and 11 remain missing.
A fishing vessel was sunk in a collision with   in the Sulu Sea. 13 crew rescued by other fishing vessels, 7 crew missing.
The cruise ship ran aground while on a voyage from Lofoten to Flåm. None of her 233 passengers and 165 crew were injured, but they were taken off the ship and transported to Ålesund.
The  coaster sank after a collision with   in the North Sea off western Denmark. Seven crewmembers jumped into the sea and were rescued by helicopters.
The tanker sank at anchor in bad weather off Diêm Điền port channel, Thái Bình Province, Vietnam in shallow water with her superstructure remaining partially above water.
The cargo ship was driven ashore at Sunda Kelapa.

The floating restaurant, usually situated in Hong Kong, capsized in the South China Sea near the Paracel Islands while under tow for restoration work. Reportedly still afloat, capsized and unsalvageable, on the 25th.
The fishing boat sank  south of Sitka, Alaska after taking on water. Its two crew were airlifted by the United States Coast Guard.

The  fishing boat capsized, and possibly sank after its anchor chain caught in its propeller  from the shore of Hungry Bay Nature Reserve, Bermuda. The single man aboard clung to the overturned hull, and was rescued by two nearby fishermen.

The ferry caught fire off Baluti Island approximately  from the port of Real, Quezon, Philippines. She burned out and was towed, beached on shore. Seven passengers dead, including the captain's mother, 120 rescued.
A fishing vessel collided with   and sank in the East China Sea  east south east of Wenzhou. Her five crew were reported missing.
A catamaran capsized in Jervis Bay, New South Wales, Australia. Of the two aboard, one man was rescued, and a body, believed to be of the second man, has been recovered.
An illegal immigrant smuggling boat sank after colliding with, or being rammed by, a Lebanese Navy patrol boat off Tripoli, Lebanon. 47 people were rescued, 7 died.
The tanker sank in the Taiwan Strait  south of Wuqui Island, Kinmen County, Taiwan. One crewman died, the other 19 were rescued.

A soil-carrying trawler, owned by the Maishadi AMS Brick Field, collided with the sand barge  on the Dakatia River during a dense fog, and promptly capsized. Five of the eleven people on board drowned, while the other six swam to shore. Murder charges were filed against the six crew of Iqbal Hossain. Four have been detained by police, while another two, including the captain, have gone into hiding.
The deck cargo ship went aground in stormy weather off Barangay Bani, Zambales, central Luzon western coast. 22 people were rescued, while the ship's captain and chief officer remained aboard.
A  ferry capsized after colliding with a larger ferry while carrying 42 passengers and three crew. 41 people were rescued, three died, and one is missing.

A trawler, with 70 people aboard, collided with the passenger launch  on the Meghna River and sank, with 10 people missing. Nine bodies were recovered. Four crew of Farhan 6 were detained by authorities, while the ship itself was detained.
A fishing vessel was cut in two and sunk when rammed by   north of Keelung, Taiwan in dense fog. All seven crew were rescued.
The  yacht sank in  of water in Glacier Bay, Alaska. The four people on board were rescued by Alaska Hunter  and then were transferred to an Sikorsky MH-60 Jayhawk helicopter from Air Station Sitka.
A migrant boat sank off the coast of Fuerteventura, Canary Islands. 40 were rescued, one died, and another 16 are missing.

Storm Corrie: The German-operated Maltese-flagged bulk carrier was abandoned while sinking at the IJmuiden outer anchorage, in the North Sea after being struck by the tanker   while at anchor in a storm. Her 18 crew were evacuated by helicopter. Julietta D was subsequently towed in to Rotterdam, South Holland, Netherlands.
The ferry capsized in the Meghna River in Narayanganj, just outside Dhaka, Bangladesh when she was struck by cargo ship  . Six dead, dozens missing.
A fishing vessel was sunk in a collision with the cargo ship   off the west coast of Taean County, South Korea, in the Yellow Sea. All 11 crew were rescued by DK Itonia.
The tugboat sank after an explosion onboard at Semoi Setawir, Sungai Sepaku River, upstream from Balikpapan, East Kalimantan, Indonesia. 4 burned, 1 missing, 7 rescued.
An inflatable boat sank off the coast of Lanzarote, Canary Islands. 51 men were rescued.
The dredge sank at Makhachkala Port, Dagestan, Russia, in the Caspian Sea in stormy weather. Crew safe.
The fishing vessel was sunk in a collision when she was towed into the path of coaster   off Tanakeke Island, south of Makassar, South Sulawesi, Indonesia. All 15 on board were rescued.
The landing craft sank in waters of Tanah Laut Regency, South Kalimantan Province, Indonesia in the Java Sea. Five of her crew were rescued, six missing.
A boat carrying 35 people capsized in Shagari, Nigeria killing 29 people.
The ferry was destroyed by fire off the west coast of Leyte. 157 passengers and 8 crew on board, all but 2 people were rescued, 1 died and 1 missing.

The freighter developed a heavy starboard list and was apparently beached with its starboard side on the bottom to prevent sinking in Chiba Prefecture waters, Honshu east coast, south of Tokyo. Her 5 crew rescued from life raft.

The  superyacht sank in Kolona Bay, Kythnos Island, Greece, in the Aegean Sea after her depth finder failed and she scraped bottom. She partially rolled over and sank, with her port side on the bottom and half of the hull remaining above waterline. Five rescued, ten missing.
The motor yacht sank under tow  off Catanzaro Marina, in the Gulf of Squillace, Calabria, Italy. All nine crew were safe.

The tourist speedboat was hit by strong waves, flooded, and capsized around 2:00 PM on a voyage from the Chàm Islands to Hội An. 17 of the 36 passengers and three crew died. A government inquiry blamed the loss of life on lack of emergency exits.

The coastal cargo ship was swamped by large waves in a storm causing her sink in shallow waters of the Van Uc River estuary, Hải Phòng, Vietnam off the Gulf of Tonkin. Her superstructure remains above water. Her five crew were rescued by Vietnam Border Guards.
The tuna longliner sank in a collision with     east of Rabaul, East New Britain province of Papua New Guinea in the Pacific Ocean. 31 crew rescued.

The fishing vessel sank off the Gulf of Guinea near Accra. The boat was carrying at least 27 people. 15 people were saved, and the captain's body was recovered. An additional 11 people were missing. The boat was carrying fish, as well as 6 Chinese and 21 Ghanaian fishermen.
The decommissioned  tugboat was sunk as an artificial reef in the Gulf of Mexico about  southeast of the Destin East Pass, Florida at a depth of about .
The tanker reported taking on water and sinking in the Arabian Sea some  west of the northwest coast of India. The crew were rescued by the Indian Coast Guard.

The cargo ship sank in shallow water with her bow above water in Phan Rang Bay during an attempted beaching following a collision with the cargo ship   off Ninh Thuận province, Vietnam. The crew were rescued by Hai Dat 36.
The superyacht was destroyed by fire and sank off Formentera, Spain.
The coaster became trapped in ice in the Sea of Okhotsk off the Shantar Archipelago. Her eight crew were rescued by a helicopter.
The floating dock listed and sank at Saka, Hiroshima Prefecture, Japan.
The bunker tanker sank off Gabès, Tunisia, in the Gulf of Gabes. The crew were rescued by the Tunisian Navy.

The trawler capsized after colliding with the passenger-launch Mitali-8  on the Meghna River. One of the four people aboard, along with the vessel's cargo of wood, was lost, while the remaining three were able to swim to shore.

The floating production storage and offloading vessel exploded, burned out, and sank in the Ukpokiti oil fields near the Escravos River. Of its 10 crew, three are confirmed dead, three have been rescued, and four are missing. The Nigerian Upstream Petroleum Regulatory Commission, a government organization, has started an investigation into the sinking.
The coastal cargo ship was sunk in a collision with the container ship   southeast of Ningbo, Zhejiang province, China in the East China Sea. One of her four crew was killed.

The decommissioned  was sunk during a sinking exercise , as part of a multinational exercise Rim of the Pacific  2022, approximately  northwest of Kauai, Hawaii. She was hit by U.S. Navy F/A-18F Super Hornets long range anti-ship missile; United States Army AH-64 Apache helicopters shot air-to-ground Hellfire missiles, rockets, and  guns; and United States Marine Corps F/A-18C/D Hornets fired AGM-88 HARM missiles, followed by a Harpoon (AGM-84) missile, and JDAMs. She was also shelled by   with its Mark 45  gun, and Japanese Self Defence Force Type 12 Surface-to-Ship Missiles and the U.S. Army High Mobility Artillery Rocket System, sinking her in  of water in the Pacific Ocean.
The container ship capsized and sank on her portside at a pier in Kolkata, India.
The cargo ship sprang a leak and sank in the Flores Sea some  off the northern coast of Sangeang Island, Bima, West Nusa Tenggara, Lesser Sunda Islands, Indonesia. Her crew was rescued.
The luxury catamaran yacht burned out at Sattahip Ocean Marina Yacht Club, Pattaya, Thailand.

The crabber vessel sprang a massive leak and sank at dock at Port of Zarubino, Primorsky Krai in the Trinity Bay, in the Sea of Japan while unloading. Her chief engineer died, the other 14 crew were rescued. Her master was hospitalized.
